CatDescriptText: The signs on the building next to the garage read, "Vote For Democratic Ticket; Superior Court (Vote For 2) - [?] son, John Morgan Davis, Mayor, David L. Lawrence, Council Vote For [?] Joseph A. McArdle - Fred W. Weir, Thomas J. Gallagher, Walter L. Demmler, A. L. Wolk".Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 10, 1945, pg. 15, reads: "GOP Workers - Republican workers of the Seventh District of the Third Ward plugged valiantly for their party, but the Democrats carried the heavier guns this time. Sixty-five per cent of the eligible voters turned out for city elections, and slightly over 30 per cent went to the polls in county. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of campaign workers for Republican Party of Seventh District of Third Ward including Leon Blackston, Alice Smalley with bow in hair, Evan Smalley wearing hat behind her, Edna Jenkins Toliver in light colored beret, her sister Lucille Jenkins Hinstead beside her, and Dave Thompkins on right standing in doorway
